    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-24T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-25T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 25, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 25—9:51 a.
                        m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. Chief<note n="36" xml:id="d300fn36">Maj. Gen. David G. Barr.</note> JUSMAG
                    informs us, your 84, January 22, that JUSMAG loses control equipment when
                    Chinese take physical delivery and has no knowledge its subsequent disposal.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 204, repeated Taipei 13.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
